To prove `Set A ∼ 𝒫 A`, we can use the fact that if a function $f$ is one-to-one, then its domain is equinumerous to its range ($A \sim \text{range}(f)$). In `HTPILib`, this theorem is typically named `equinum_range`.

The proof strategy is:
1.  Rewrite the goal `Set A ∼ 𝒫 A` using the equality `range (val_image A) = 𝒫 A` (from Lemma 14) to become `Set A ∼ range (val_image A)`.
